  "prompt": "How was Google maps developed?",
  "response": "Google Maps was developed through several key stages:\n\n1. Initial Acquisition (2004)\n- Google acquired a mapping startup called Where 2 Technologies\n- The founders Lars and Jens Rasmussen led the initial development\n- They originally conceived the project as a desktop application\n\n2. Early Development\n- Transformed from desktop software to web-based service\n- Launched in February 2005 as a web mapping service\n- Initially covered the United States, then expanded globally\n\n3. Key Technical Innovations\n- Used satellite imagery from various providers\n- Developed advanced mapping and navigation technologies\n- Incorporated street view capabilities\n- Created algorithms for routing and location data\n\n4. Major Expansion Features\n- Added satellite and terrain views\n- Integrated GPS and real-time traffic information\n- Developed mobile app versions\n- Added business listings and reviews\n- Implemented street view and 360-degree imagery\n\n5. Ongoing Improvements\n- Continuously updated with new mapping data\n- Enhanced location accuracy\n- Added machine learning for better navigation\n- Integrated AI and crowd-sourced information\n\nThe development was a gradual process of technological innovation, strategic acquisitions, and continuous improvement, transforming from a simple mapping service to a comprehensive navigation and location platform.",
